-- Brazilian Stock Movers: BR Malls, Gafisa and Vale Are Active
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2012-04-02T20:24:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/brazilian-stock-movers-br-malls-gafisa-and-vale-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index added 1.1 percent to 65,216.25.  BR Malls Participacoes SA (BRML3)  (BRML3 BS) advanced 3.2 percent
to 24.54 reais.  Brazil ’s biggest owner of shopping malls sold a
10 percent stake in Pantanal Shopping for 45 million reais
($24.6 million), according to a regulatory filing.  Gafisa SA (GFSA3)  (GFSA3 BS) tumbled 4.2 percent to 4.12 reais. The
homebuilder posted a loss of 1.05 billion reais in 2011,
according to preliminary results released yesterday. It was
expected to report a profit of 104 million reais, the average
estimate of 14 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  Vale SA (VALE5)  (VALE5 BS) climbed 2.6 percent to 42.55 reais.
Manufacturing activity rose to a one-year high in  China ,
according to a purchasing managers’ index compiled by the
country’s logistics federation and the National Bureau of
Statistics. China is Vale’s biggest export market.  To contact the reporter on this story:
